ABIDJAN -Â More than 150 migrants have returned to Ivory Coast from Libya after reports of slave trading.
	
	A CNN report from Tripoli sent shockwaves through sub-Saharan Africa, angering many countries. The channel recently aired footage of what appeared to be an auction of men, offered to Libyan buyers as farmhands. READ: 'Slavery has no place in our world': UN chief on Libya slave auctions The migrants were allegedly sold for just over R5,000. Burkina Faso has now recalled its ambassador to Libya. Niger wants the matter to be debated at the EU-Africa summit later this month. eNCA